Node.Notes: Uncertain. Perhaps name for a type of psalm. Speculation of relation to a verb meaning to stray leads to suggestion of a "wandering" style of psalm.
No mention of this person in extant texts, though David is known to have experienced opposition from Benjamites (see 1 Samuel 24-26 and 2 Sam 16:5; 20:1).

Node.Notes: Some think "glory" is one way of speaking of an individual because parallel with "sou" and "life" here.
Text reads "upon me" in the sense of the integrity that is in me. Many change text to "O Most High."
(SYNTAX) While some occurrences may function as substantives, this is a hiphil particple, which is what is needed here.
